My other challenge isn’t trying to find products to make my skin healthy; rather, it’s trying to stay within my $20 budget!

Until I leave home, my biggest issue is oral hygiene. I’ve been battling with expensive toothpaste, pricey retainer paste and disposable mouthguards for over a decade, so I turned to the supermarket to find some cheaper alternatives that do the job!

MisakoB writes:

Looking at the history of hygiene products in Japan, I really admire how efficient is one brand that cleans the toilet. This company set up a system where householders put in some money, select 6 fighters and a villain, and the toilet cleaning team comes every few months and blitzes the bathroom!

Depends came to the rescue when I was unable to use a tampon and arranged to have some given to me. This confused me because people were acting wierd around me, on the plane and at school. My first school friend would never come near me although we were talking. When I called out on the fact that using a tampon is not somehow disfiguring him when I used to use a pad, I finally got him to explain it.
